The paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the construction and analysis of Vietoris-Rips complexes, which is a common topic in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms for computing persistent homology, which is a topic in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of convexity and differentiability of curves suggests a connection to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. The mention of homotopy type and running time analysis suggests a connection to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques to improve running time suggests a connection to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
